25:08.419 --> 25:10.121
We've heard that a few times this morning.

25:12.144 --> 25:14.207
There's no power that he doesn't possess.

25:15.649 --> 25:16.710
He is limitless.

25:17.651 --> 25:19.534
He's in time, old time, every time.

25:21.437 --> 25:25.662
All the time he has everything that his children need.

25:25.943 --> 25:27.725
There's nothing that he can't provide.

25:28.006 --> 25:29.007
He is sovereign.

25:30.389 --> 25:31.250
So he is.

25:32.194 --> 25:37.281
What he can do for exceeds anything that we could ever dream of or imagine.

25:37.842 --> 25:42.909
Our prayers to him can be answered in ways that we would never have even begin to think about.

25:45.572 --> 25:47.335
His working in us is unlimited.

25:50.179 --> 25:55.827
What he's able to do in us is also beyond our comprehension.

25:59.131 --> 26:01.234
Gospel to John helps us out with this and

26:01.826 --> 26:16.361
Verse 14, excuse me, chapter 14, verses 12 to 14 says this, very truly, I tell you, whoever believes in me will do the works I have been doing, and they will do even greater things than these because I am going to the Father.

26:17.262 --> 26:22.027
And I will do whatever you ask in my name so that the Father may be glorified in the Son.

26:22.788 --> 26:25.531
You may ask me for anything in my name, and I will do it.

26:27.973 --> 26:28.914
Now, of course,

26:28.994 --> 26:44.031
passage of scripture is talking about being within the will of God, but it's all in itself could be a message, but it helps us realize more about the magnitude of the glory of the God that we serve.

26:45.633 --> 26:47.295
He deserves our praise, doesn't he?

26:49.077 --> 26:49.818
He deserves it.

26:49.898 --> 26:57.106
We should be thankful to him in all of his glory in this season of focusing in on giving thanks,

26:57.826 --> 27:02.754
We should be mindful of being thankful in all things, shouldn't we?

27:04.256 --> 27:05.758
